  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">LAC and MENA Regional (Algeria, Ecuador, Egypt, Jordan, Lebanon, Mexico, Morocco, Peru, Tunisia): Strengthening and Expanding HIV-Related Legal Services and Rights &#x2013; Phase Out</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">1) To strengthen regional collaboration for the quality and sustainability of HIV-related legal services and rights; and 2) To strengthen the capacity of partners to advocate for an improved legal and policy environment for HIV prevention and treatment.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Proposed civil society organizations identified for support in each country; people living with HIV and members of key affected populations.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project aimed at documenting IDLO&apos;s work on HIV-related legal services and rights in the LAC and MENA regions to-date, share best practices and lessons learned, and support its local partners to transition to other sources of funding.</narrative>
  </description>
